        "id": "d19893eb9279ad31",
        "text": "Society does not rise like leaven, it does not become uniformly larger, more differentiated, more complex, as the theories of progress of the 19th century thought (and could think, because they understood society only as an economic system). Rather, it complexifies some functional areas and leaves others atrophied. This imbalance has always been the occasion for a critique of civilization - be it, like the philosophy of restoration, on religion or, like Habermas, on reason. However, recent cybernetic and systems-theoretical research shows that this is a quite normal phenomenon which can only be corrected by evolution."
